Installation
============

Execute on the terminal:
./configure
make
make install

Dependencies
============

- liblo (http://liblo.sourceforge.net/)

Usage
=====

Put the controlfromosc element in the pipeline. Example:
gst-launch -v -m fakesrc ! controlfromosc port=7770 ! fakesink silent=TRUE

It will accept the following OSC messages:

Set
===
/set ss* element_name property new_value OR
/set/element_name/property * new_value
(* can be i, f, s, h, d, c, T, F. Set it accordingly to the property type)

Sets the 'property' on 'element_name' to 'new_value'.

Get
===

/get ssss element_name property reply_address reply_port OR
/get/element_name/propery ss reply_address reply_port

Asks for the current value of 'property' on 'element_name'. Reply is sent to
'reply_address:reply_port' as an OSC message formatted like: '/get/reply ss*
element_name property current_value'.

Subscribe
=========

/subscribe ssss element_name property reply_address reply_port OR
/subscribe/element_name/property ss reply_address reply_port

Subscribes to the 'property' of 'element_name'. It will receive a
reply upon subscription confirming it '/subscribe/reply sss "subscribed" 
element_name property'.

After that, every change in the property will send a message '/subscre/reply ss*
element_name property current_value' to every computer subscribed.

Unsubscribe
===========

/unsubscribe ssss element_name property reply_address reply_port
/unsubscribe/element_name/property ss reply_address reply_port

Unsubscribes a computer to the 'property' of 'element_name'. It will receive a
reply confirming it won't receive updates anymore '/unsubscribe/reply sss
"unsubscribed" element_name property'.

Control
=======

/control ss*d element_name property new_value time_to_set_in_seconds
/control/element_name/property *d new_value time_to_set_in_seconds

Sets the 'property' on 'element_name' to 'new_value' in
'time_to_set_in_seconds'.

Locate
======

/locate d seek_time_in_seconds

Performs a seek.

Pause
=====

/pause

Pauses the pipeline.

Play
====

/play

Plays the pipeline.
